#This file contains notes on shell scripting

#### Simple commands :-

#	whoami				<display user>
#	pwd				<Present working directory>
#	cd PATH				<Change directory>
#	file FILENAME			<Display the type of the file>
#	type [-a] COMMAND		<Display information about a command; a flag shows all the info>
#	hostname			<Displays host name>

### ls command:~

#This command is used to list the contents of a directory
#Useage : ls SampleDirectory/

#   Flags

#    a		<Lists all files including hidden files>
#    d		<Lists info about the directory>
#    t		
